frameDefinitions: An Earner receives Earnings by providing Goods to a Buyer; providing the Goods also generally entails a cost, which may or may not be included in the consideration.
A Figure is located essentially at the same location as a Ground, which is viewed as point-like, or having no important internal or external structure.
The words of this frame describe how a Resource_controller spends money or other Resources for a particular purpose .
This frame concerns transparent nouns that denote Instances of Types of entities or events.
A Political_region, often a nation,  has an economic system, theEconomy, defined by the level of production and consumption of goods and services.
A Product is offered by a Seller at a particular Price such that some total cost for the Buyer in the transaction is a multiple of the Price.
frameExamples: This reflects the 15 % jump in <t><fex name='Earnings'>earnings</fex></t> over 1994 .

The survey confirmed that management interference in team operations had increased , and <t><fex name='Instance'>instances</fex></t> of management decisions being taken without team consultation had also increased .
The Canadian <t><fex name='Economy'>economy</fex></t> will continue to expand in 2005.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Earner</fen> is involved in a transaction or set of transactions as the party that receives payment.
<fen>Earnings</fen> are the money given to the <fen>Earner</fen> in a transaction, generally in exchange for <fen>Goods</fen>.
The time when the <fen>Earner</fen> makes their <fen>Earnings</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Earner</fen> makes their <fen>Earnings</fen>.
The <fen>Ground</fen> serves as a basis for describing the location of the <fen>Figure</fen>.
The <fen>Figure</fen> is perceived as located relative to a certain <fen>Ground</fen> location. The <fen>Figure</fen> can be an entity or an event.
The period of time during which the locative relation between <fen>Figure</fen> and <fen>Ground</fen> obtains.

The <fen>Resource_controller</fen> is the individual whose frugality or generosity is being described. Person typically occurs as the External Argument or, in some cases when <fen>Behavior</fen> is also expressed, in an <ment>of</ment>-PP:
Some specific <fen>Behavior</fen> may be described as frugal or extravagant, rather than attributing the characteristic directly to the <fen>Resource_controller</fen>.
This role is the resource which the <fen>Resource_controller</fen> expends.
A thing or episode of a certain <fen>Type</fen>.
The category of thing or event of which an <fen>Instance</fen> is picked out.
The <fen>Political_region</fen> is the nation, state, or other political body within which an economic system exists.
The <fen>Economy</fen> is the state of the <fen>Political_region</fen> as defined by the production, consumption, etc. of goods and services.
A commodity, item, or service being sold by the <fen>Seller</fen> at a certain <fen>Price</fen>.
The amount of money that the <fen>Seller</fen> charges the <fen>Buyer</fen> for a <fen>Product</fen>.
listRoleExamples: She made a lot of money <fex>in Africa</fex> .
He was at my shop <fex>on Friday</fex>.
It's thrifty of Jo <fex>to re-use teabags</fex>.
I collected two <t>specimens</t> <fex>of this rare species</fex>.
The rate <fex>for second hand products</fex> is just too high.
She sells seashells at a rate <fex>of $20 per pound</fex>.
